  // prev 10.235.0 — zone-conflict fix for un-wearable items. An item the pet cannot wear (wrong body / alt-style token, e.g. Tahini\'s Peachy Filter on body 1274) was still WINNING its zone in getVisibleLayers and EVICTING a worn item it has no business replacing — the "Removed by Dyeworks White" thought bubble that then could not be re-selected. Now incompatible items are excluded from the zone-conflict loop entirely (via _appFitsBody), so they neither render nor remove other items, and the displaced item stays selectable. Canonical pets (no bodyId) unchanged. NOTE: if a pet switch still shows the OLD pet in the animated preview, that is the 10.234 _busy rebuild-drop fix — make sure you are on 10.234+. Builds on 10.234. Roll back to 10.234/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.234.0 — unified badge + _busy rebuild-drop race fix. Tahini\'s path still said "(wrong body/style)" while Leif said "Can\'t be worn by this pet"; now BOTH say "Can\'t be worn by this pet". And fixed the _busy REBUILD-DROP race: a rebuild requested mid-build (item toggled / pet switched) was DROPPED, leaving a stale overlay over the new static layers — that is the "Banana horns appear then vanish" flicker and items missing after a fast switch. The rebuild is now QUEUED (via _pendingRebuild) and re-run from enable() finally once the in-flight build finishes, so the LATEST composite always wins. Builds on 10.233. Roll back to 10.233/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.233.0 — PET-SWITCH STALE-RENDER FIX (multi-agent diagnosis). Root cause: renderPreview is async (debounce + layer fetches); a still-in-flight render for the OLD pet finished AFTER you clicked the new pet and stamped the OLD pet HTML into the NEW pet snap_* (no generation guard), while the content-only signature let loadPet restore that poisoned snapshot and skip the redraw — so static render, item list, AND the animated overlay (which composites from the live static layers) all stayed on the old pet. Fix (surgical, renderPreview only): (1) capture _renderGen/_renderPet at render start; (2) abandon a render whose pet/generation changed during its awaits; (3) fold the active pet into the redraw signature; (4) write the snapshot keyed to the render pet and only if still current. So switching pets reliably redraws everything — and the overlay following the now-correct static layers means all worn items (incl. static-only like Banana horns) come along. Builds on 10.232. Roll back to 10.232/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.232.0 — unified badge + Previewing-with label. // also: (confirmed working on the homepage haul). (1) UNIFIED the "can\'t be worn" badge: Leif (species/color miss) and Tahini (wrong token body) are the same situation to the user, so both now say "Can\'t be worn by this pet" instead of two different texts. (2) ITEM-PAGE preview now shows the "Previewing with {petname}" label (it lived inside the hidden .tryon-mode-wrap); the cog/refetch/clear buttons stay hidden as before, so you just see which pet is loaded. Builds on 10.231. Roll back to 10.231/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.231.0 — REAL FIX: pet-body match. Tahini\'s item layer is bodyId 67 but Tahini\'s pet bodyId is 1274 (its unconverted-token/alt-style body) — mismatch, so it can\'t wear it. pose was HAPPY_FEM, so 10.229\'s UNCONVERTED guess was the wrong field. Now, when a pet has a KNOWN body (bodyId set — alt-style/special/token pets), an item is only worn/animated if it\'s modelled for THAT body: pet bodyId in the item\'s compatibleBodies, or it offers a matching/universal layer. Canonical pets (no bodyId, e.g. Mina) still trust appearanceOn — no second-guessing (that was the Mina regression). Applied consistently to getVisibleLayers (static), _itemWearReason (badge), and resolveMovieMap (animation). pet-dbg removed. Builds on 10.230. Roll back to 10.230/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.230.0 — PET-DBG diagnostic. 10.229 assumed "unconverted token style" = pose UNCONVERTED, but Tahini still wears items, so that field is wrong. [DTR pet-dbg] now dumps the full petData (pose, bodyId, state, species/color, every key) + the staged item\'s layer bodyIds on each render, so we can see EXACTLY how the unconverted/alt-style appearance is represented and gate on the right field. Keeps 10.229. Builds on 10.229. Roll back to 10.229/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.229.0 — UNCONVERTED rule. Tahini & Leif wear unconverted token styles, and DTI hides body-specific item layers on UNCONVERTED pets (impress-2020 getVisibleLayers). The static render already did this (Tahini showed only the body), but two paths ignored it: (1) the "can\'t be worn" badge only checked appearanceOn layers, so it missed unconverted; (2) the animation\'s movie-only path rendered the item anyway. Now both honor it: new _itemWearReason flags species/COLOR incompatibility (0 layers, e.g. Baby colors) AND unconverted+body-specific, used by the badge on click and on every pet switch; resolveMovieMap skips body-specific item movies on unconverted pets (queries bodyId). So Tahini now correctly warns + doesn\'t animate the Peachy Filter; Mina (converted, compatible) still wears it. Builds on 10.228. Roll back to 10.228/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.228.0 — diagnostic removed; compat confirmed. The 10.227 badge-dbg proved item 85175 on Tahini (species 18 = Hissi, color 37) returns 1 layer status ok => wearable; the animation even loaded hissi-thought_bubble.js. Leif (species 46) returns 0 layers and the "X only" species list literally includes Hissi — so DTI itself says Tahini CAN wear it. No warning on Tahini is correct DTI behavior; warning on Leif is correct. Removed the [DTR badge-dbg] logging. Warning still refreshes on pet switch (10.226). Builds on 10.227. Roll back to 10.227/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.227.0 — BADGE DIAGNOSTIC. Tahini still shows no warning, so [DTR badge-dbg] now logs, on every render: whether _refreshAllWlBadges runs + how many WL rows it finds, and per item the pet species/color + how many layers appearanceOn returned + status + whether it would warn. This tells us definitively whether the refresh isn\'t finding the row vs appearanceOn genuinely returning layers for Tahini (= DTI thinks it IS compatible). Builds on 10.226. Roll back to 10.226/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.226.0 — WARNING REFRESHES ON PET SWITCH. Confirmed against impress-2020\'s resolver: appearanceOn(species,color) returns ZERO layers when an item is not modelled for that pet ("if it does not fit the pet, we return an empty ItemAppearance with no layers"). So the 10.225 wearability test (0 layers) is correct — the real bug was that the badge was only computed inside _hpTryonToggleItem (on click), so switching pets never re-evaluated it. That is why Leif needed a click and Tahini showed nothing. Now renderPreview re-checks every staged WL row against the CURRENT pet on each render (cached per pet), so the species/color warning appears/clears on pet switch with no click. Builds on 10.225. Roll back to 10.225/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.225.0 — DTI-FAITHFUL COMPAT. Read impress-2020 getVisibleLayers: it does NOT compare a layer bodyId to the pet body — compatibility is decided UPSTREAM by item.appearanceOn(species,color), and the frontend just trusts it (only hides body-specific item layers when the pet is UNCONVERTED or the zone is pet-restricted). The client-side "layer.bodyId === petData.bodyId" filter (added here, not in DTI) was the whole bug: it hid valid items (special-color Krawk) and wrongly warned wearable pets (Mina). Reverted 10.220/10.223/10.224 compat experiments. Now: render trusts appearanceOn (DTI cross-compat baked in); the "can\'t be worn" badge shows only when appearanceOn returns NO layers. render-dbg removed. Builds on 10.224. Roll back to 10.224/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.224.0 — WARNING/RENDER PARITY (reverted; non-DTI bodyId logic). The "Can\'t be worn by this species/color" badge fired on ONE condition (layers.length === 0), so it showed for Leif (0 layers) but NOT Tahini (1 body-mismatched layer) even though the renderer hides both. Now the badge uses the SAME compatible-bodies test as getVisibleLayers, so badge and render always agree — Tahini now shows the warning too. (The badge is still attached by the async toggle, so it appears once the pet + item appearance finish loading, not literally on the first synchronous paint — it needs the pet\'s species/color over the network.) Builds on 10.223. Roll back to 10.223/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.223.0 — COMPATIBILITY REGRESSION FIX. 10.220 relaxed the bodyId filter to keep a body-divergent layer when no other layer covered its zone — but that is NOT a compatibility check, so items that genuinely cannot be worn by a species/color (e.g. Peachy Filter on Tahini) leaked through. Now we gate on the item\'s real compatible-bodies list (fetchItemLayers already fetched it, we now keep it): a body-divergent layer is kept ONLY if the item is actually compatible (offers a matching/universal layer OR the pet body is in its compatible-bodies). Otherwise every layer is hidden. Special-color Krawk (body 1259 wearing body-150 items) still works; incompatible species/color is correctly hidden. render-dbg now prints compat[...]. Builds on 10.222. Roll back to 10.222/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.222.0 — RE-TOGGLE FIX. Turning animation OFF then ON left most layers blank/wrong because mountMovieLayer grabbed AdobeAn.compositions[lastKey], assuming the bundle just registered a composition. True on first load; on re-toggle the <script> is CACHED so loadScript returns without re-registering, and every layer grabbed the same (last) composition. Now we remember movieUrl -> compId from the first load and reuse it, so each layer maps to its own movie on every toggle. Keeps 10.221 note polish + render-dbg. Builds on 10.221. Roll back to 10.221/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.221.0 — loading-note polish + render diagnostic. (1) The "Loading animation…" note is now a small top-anchored pill instead of a big centered block — the still-visible static preview is never blocked while the animation loads. (Confirmed the static layers are only hidden AFTER every layer mounts, so a blank-while-loading look means the STATIC outfit itself didn\'t render.) (2) New concise [DTR render-dbg] line per render: for each worn/tryon item, how many layers are visible vs total + the bodyId(s) + ZONELOST flag — to pinpoint why a pet\'s worn items don\'t show (e.g. Leif). Builds on 10.220. Roll back to 10.220/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.220.0 — TRY-ON APPLY FIX (bodyId). Diagnostic proved it: the tried-on item layer had bodyId 150, hasImg true, but visible false because the pet appearance body was 1259 (a special-color Krawk whose items model on body 150 while the pet appearance is body 1259). getVisibleLayers strictly required layer.bodyId === petData.bodyId and hid the item. Fix: a body-mismatched item layer is now dropped ONLY if a body-matching layer covers the same zone; otherwise we trust appearanceOn(species,color) — the server\'s own per-pet query that already validated compatibility — and keep it, so the item shows. Diagnostic log removed. Builds on 10.218/10.219. Roll back to 10.218/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.219.0 — TRY-ON DIAGNOSTIC. Bug: clicking Try On selects the item but its layer is not applied to the pet preview (e.g. the Dyeworks Filter thought bubble). The item DOES win its zone conflict (it removes the old thought bubble) but its own layer never renders statically. New [DTR tryon-dbg] log prints, for the tried-on item: each layer\'s depth/bodyId/zone/has-image/visible + the pet bodyId/pose + restricted zones — so we can see exactly which filter drops it. Keeps the 10.218 live-rebuild + multi-item + persist. Builds on 10.218. Roll back to 10.218/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.218.0 — ANIMATION: LIVE REBUILD + MULTI-ITEM + PERSIST. Three connected fixes for the stale-snapshot bugs. (1) MULTI-ITEM is back (was wrongly blamed in 10.214 — the real culprit was the root.framerate freeze, gone since 10.216): resolveMovieMap queries the viewed item AND every other worn item via _hpTryonWornItemIds, so ALL animated worn items move. (2) LIVE REBUILD: when the outfit changes (item add/remove) or the pet switches, the static preview re-render now tears the overlay down AND rebuilds from the new layers — so a removed item stops animating, the remaining ones start, and switching pets works while Animate is on. (3) PERSIST: the Animate toggle is now a GM-persisted DESIRE — it stays on across pets/pages until toggled off, and auto-enables each new preview. Builds on 10.217. Roll back to 10.217/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.217.0 — ANIMATION: MOVIE-ONLY LAYERS. Diagnostic on item 85175 (a Dyeworks thought-bubble Filter) showed its animated layer at depth 51 but the static composite at depths [3,4,6,18,49,50,52] — no 51 — so "0 animated" AND the item looked un-applied. These filter items render ONLY as an animated movie (no static image at that depth). Fix: build() now also renders movie depths that have NO matching static layer, each as its own animated <canvas> at its zone depth — so the item both shows and animates. Items that DO have a static layer (e.g. 70901) are unchanged. Keeps the 10.216 unfreeze + throttle. Single-item. Builds on 10.216. Roll back to 10.216/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.216.0 — ANIMATION: UNFREEZE + correct speed. Root cause of the 10.214/10.215 break: root.framerate = fps FROZE these AdobeAn roots, so build() hid the static layers under a frozen blank overlay = the item looked un-tried-on AND nothing moved. Removed root.framerate entirely (restores the SpriteSheet-fix build\'s PLAYING behavior). Speed (the "too fast/aggro" issue) is now fixed the safe way: each stage.update() advances one frame, and we THROTTLE update() to ~props.fps via the Ticker clock — pure RAF, no clip-framerate games. Single item still (multi-item returns later). Builds on 10.213. Roll back to 10.213/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.215.0 — ANIMATION: REGRESSION REVERT. 10.214 broke a working animation two ways: RAF_SYNCHED froze it ("nothing moves") and the multi-item query removed items. Both reverted to the known-good 10.213 path, keeping ONLY the correct speed fix: PURE RAF (like impress-2020) + root.framerate = props.fps per clip, so the single viewed item animates at the right speed. Multi-item (all worn items animating) will return as a separate, carefully-tested step. Builds on 10.213. Roll back to 10.213/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.214.0 — ANIMATION: SPEED + MULTI-ITEM (reverted; RAF_SYNCHED + multi-item regressed). 10.213 animated but (a) ran way too fast and (b) only the page\'s item moved. Fixes: (1) SPEED — pure RAF fires at the monitor refresh (60/120/144Hz) and ignores fps, so the clip advanced one frame per refresh; now Ticker uses RAF_SYNCHED and each root gets root.framerate = props.fps so playback is time-based at the authored rate on any display. (2) MULTI-ITEM — resolveMovieMap now queries EVERY item on the pet (viewed + worn outfit + try-on + picker, via new window._hpTryonWornItemIds()) plus the pet body, so all animated worn items move together, not just the one. Builds on 10.213. Roll back to 10.213/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.213.0 — ANIMATION, ROOT CAUSE FIXED. The diagnostic showed the bundle symbols are [Bitmap3, Tween1-3, novastar, allitem_foreground_higher, Stage] but MovieClip candidates was EMPTY — every constructor threw. Cause: the manifest handler never built the createjs.SpriteSheet objects from lib.ssMetadata, so Sprite.gotoAndStop() hit getNumFrames() on undefined. Fixes: (1) build SpriteSheets from lib.ssMetadata exactly like AdobeAn handleComplete; (2) the export symbol is allitem_foreground_higher — Adobe keeps underscores, strips only the DASH, so derive via replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9_]/g,\'\') first; (3) use the bundle\'s own lib.Stage. Now the symbols construct and the timeline ticks. Builds on 10.212. Roll back to 10.212/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.212.0 — ANIMATION SYMBOL RESOLVER, robust + diagnostic. The filename guess (allitemforegroundhigher) is not the symbol name for this bundle, so resolution kept missing. Now the fallback try-INSTANTIATES every non-CachedBmp symbol, keeps the ones that build into a real MovieClip (gotoAndPlay), and picks the one with the MOST frames (the main timeline) — no name guessing. It also LOGS the full non-CachedBmp symbol list + the MovieClip candidates with frame counts, so the actual export symbol is visible in [DTR anim]. Builds on 10.211. Roll back to 10.211/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.211.0 — ANIMATION SYMBOL FIX #2 + stuck-banner fix. (1) 10.210 derived the export symbol with replace(non-alnum -> "_"), but impress-2020 REMOVES non-alnums entirely: all-item_foreground_higher -> allitemforegroundhigher. 10.210 missed and fell back to a Bitmap3 sub-graphic whose constructor throws getNumFrames. Now we try the stripped name (and the underscore variant), and the last-resort scan try-INSTANTIATES candidates, skipping CachedBmp/Bitmap/Shape, accepting only a real MovieClip (gotoAndPlay). (2) The "Loading animation…" banner got stuck because enable() only cleared the note on success; on failure it now shows a brief "No animation available" that auto-clears. Builds on 10.210. Roll back to 10.210/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.210.0 — ANIMATION SYMBOL FIX: 10.209 matched + preloaded the manifest but chose the WRONG export symbol ("Stage", a createjs.Stage subclass) because it looked the timeline up by composition id (a hex string that is NOT a symbol name). impress-2020 names the export root after the movie FILENAME (sanitized): all-item_foreground_higher.js -> lib.all_item_foreground_higher. Now we derive the symbol from the filename FIRST, then the comp id, then a guess that EXCLUDES CachedBmp_*/Stage — so the real animated timeline instantiates and actually moves. Builds on 10.209. Roll back to 10.209/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.209.0 — ANIMATED PREVIEW, TWO BUG FIXES. (1) MATCHING: the movie map was keyed by imageUrlV2 and matched against each static layer\'s rendered img src, but animated layers often expose a null/size-mismatched imageUrlV2 (currentSrc vs src, idealSize suffix), so every layer missed and the toggle reported "0 animated" on items that DO animate. Now the map is keyed by ZONE DEPTH (the integer): the static preview sets img.style.zIndex = zone.depth, and the GraphQL layers carry zone { depth }, so depth is a stable join. movieByDepth = Map(String(depth) -> canvasMovieLibraryUrl); build() matches each static layer by String(layer.z) (imageUrlV2 kept only as a fallback). (2) PLAYBACK: a matched layer mounted but sat FROZEN because mountMovieLayer guessed the export symbol by name regex (often a static support graphic, not the main timeline) and never preloaded the bundle\'s image manifest (so even the right symbol had no bitmaps bound). Rewrote it to mirror impress-2020 OutfitMovieLayer: AdobeAn.getComposition(id).getLibrary(), PRELOAD lib.properties.manifest via a createjs.LoadQueue then AdobeAn.compositionLoaded(props.id), instantiate the export symbol named after props.id, run the createjs.Ticker at lib.properties.fps, and advance the playhead via stage.update(evt). Builds on 10.208. Roll back to 10.208/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.208.0 — ANIMATION FIX: the composite rendered but didn\'t move. The per-layer tick handler called stage.update() with NO event, so the MovieClip never got the timing delta and froze on frame 1. Now it passes the tick event (stage.update(evt)) AND kicks the exported root into play() / gotoAndPlay(0) — the timeline actually advances. Builds on 10.207. Roll back to 10.207/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.207.0 — ANIMATED PREVIEW: the item-page Try-On preview now has a clean "Animate" on/off toggle (replaces the old "Animate (beta)" button). ON builds a multi-layer animated composite of the CURRENT previewed pet + worn item: it reads the exact static layer stack the preview already resolved (inheriting DTI zone-conflict order), resolves each layer\'s canvasMovieLibraryUrl via impress-2020 GraphQL (pet appearance + item appearance), and for every animated layer renders a CreateJS movie on a <canvas> (else a static <img>), all stacked in zone-depth z-order on ONE shared createjs.Ticker so they play in sync. OFF tears down every stage + ticker listener and restores the static <img> stack — repeatable, no leaked canvases/tickers. All-static items show a "nothing to animate" note and stay off. Also: a CONSERVATIVE guard skips init/style-injection when the script runs inside the strict-CSP customization preview iframe (kills the CSP console flood). Builds on 10.206. Roll back to 10.206/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.206.0 — SPIKE: Animate button no longer JUMPS on click. The button + the animation host shared one absolute bar, so rendering the movie grew the bar and shoved the button up. Now the bar holds only the button (fixed at bottom of the pet, z-index:7) and the animation host is a SEPARATE absolute overlay (inset:0, z-index:5, pointer-events:none) — the button stays put while the movie/note renders behind it. (Spike already CONFIRMED feasible: CreateJS + images.neopets.com movie library load with no CSP block and play on canvas.) Builds on 10.205. Roll back to 10.205/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.205.0 — SPIKE note readability: the "No animation available"/status note was gray (#5a6b62) text directly over the pet art — unreadable. Now a white rounded pill (rgba(255,255,255,.96)) with dark ink text + soft shadow, legible over any pet image. (Spike confirmed working: it correctly queried the data path and reported this static item has 0 animated layers; CreateJS/CSP still untested until an ANIMATED item is tried.) Builds on 10.204. Roll back to 10.204/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.204.0 — SPIKE button VISIBILITY fix: the "Animate (beta)" button mounted (console confirmed) but was invisible because it was appended INSIDE .tryon-canvas-wrap, which is a square with overflow:hidden — so it got clipped. Now it is an absolute overlay anchored bottom-center of the pet image (within the visible square), with the canvas-wrap promoted to position:relative. Builds on 10.203. Roll back to 10.203/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.203.0 — CLEANUP + SPIKE. (1) CLEANUP: hide the native "Customize with Your Neopet" customizer block at the BOTTOM of the item page (#dia-preview-card, which holds turbo-frame#item-preview) via html.dia-itemv2-scoped display:none. NO DOM deleted — the node stays for safety; the item-page Try-On preview does NOT use turbo-frame#item-preview at all (it renders impress-2020 GraphQL imageUrlV2 PNGs as <img> in .tryon-layers, and #dtr-tophat / #dia-tryon-picker-drawer live under #dia-hp-page / body, not inside the customizer), so hiding it cannot break the preview. (2) SPIKE: experimental "Animate (beta)" button mounted into the item-page Try-On preview header. On click it resolves the CURRENT item id, queries impress-2020 GraphQL for the layer canvasMovieLibraryUrl (the CreateJS movie-library .js on images.neopets.com), and if present loads CreateJS + the bundle via NATIVE <script> tags and plays it on a <canvas>. Graceful "no animation available" on static items / missing library / CSP. All wrapped in try/catch, every step console.logs with a [DTR anim spike] prefix. Never breaks the page. Builds on 10.202. Roll back to 10.202/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.202.0 — TWO item-page Try-On preview bug fixes: (1) DIMMING restored — 10.200 had hidden #dtr-toh-backdrop under html.dia-itemv2, so the rest of the page no longer dimmed behind the preview; removed that hide so the backdrop dims again. (2) DRAG fix — the Custom Canvas picker (#dia-tryon-picker-drawer) detached when dragging because it was missing from the _haulItemDrag element set; added it so all four panels (tryon + wl + tophat + picker drawer) move together. Builds on 10.201. Roll back to 10.201/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.201.0 — TWO item-page Try-On fixes (html.dia-itemv2-scoped only; homepage/closet TOH untouched). FIX 1 — restore the pet selector + Custom Canvas picker that 10.200 over-hid: 10.200 hid ALL of #dtr-tophat (which bundles .tryon-header [title bar + X], .tryon-roster-wrap [the pet-thumbnail ROSTER the user clicks to switch pets], and .tryon-mode-wrap [the "Previewing with…" chrome]) AND hid #dia-tryon-picker-drawer. Now #dtr-tophat stays VISIBLE; only .tryon-header + .tryon-mode-wrap are hidden, so the ROSTER (pet selector) shows. #dia-tryon-picker-drawer (the "CUSTOM CANVAS ITEMS" list) is UN-HIDDEN. Kept hidden: the tabs (ctx.sources stays null), the wl .dia-wl-header / .dia-wl-footer / quick-add, the candy-stripe ::before banners, and the closet dimmer. Net: pet preview + pet selector + Custom Canvas list + the single item row, but NO tab strip and NO title-header bars. FIX 2 — Save button moved from LEFT to BOTTOM-RIGHT: the #dia-action-row is a sibling of the OWNED/WANTED grid under #dia-work-card, but its only CSS was scoped to "#dia-item-card-v2 #dia-action-row" (wrong ancestor → never matched → plain left-aligned block button under the OWNED column). Re-scoped under #dtr-header-split #dia-work-card #dia-action-row as a full-width flex strip with justify-content:flex-end so Save sits bottom-right under BOTH columns. Builds on 10.200. Roll back to 10.200/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.200.0 — ITEM-PAGE Try On is now a MINIMAL, EPHEMERAL single-item preview (Approach A: strip the existing #dia-hp-tryon-panel + #dia-hp-wl-panel cluster with html.dia-itemv2-scoped CSS, no new render engine). (1) NO tabs — the wl source-filter bar (.dia-wl-srcbar) is hidden on the item page. (2) NO headers — #dtr-tophat (the pet-preview header + roster + mode-wrap), the wl header bar (.dia-wl-header), the wl footer (Clear Haul), the quickadd block, the Custom Canvas drawer (#dia-tryon-picker-drawer) and the closet modal dimmer (#dtr-toh-backdrop) are all hidden here. (3) ONLY THIS item shows in the right list: the item-page ctx.loadHaulItems returns ONE ephemeral row {this item} held in a local var, never DTR_HAUL.all(); the row keeps its × remove. (4) EPHEMERAL — the preview NO LONGER calls DTR_HAUL.add; it seeds the pet via _dtrTohSeedItems (which only fetches layers by id, no DTR_HAUL membership) and renders the single row from the local item, so the user real haul lists are untouched. On close we also defensively DTR_HAUL.remove(itemId,homepage) any stray legacy entry. (5) DRAGGABLE — a small item-page pointer-drag (_haulItemDrag) moves the preview + row panels together by translate(); _makeDraggable early-returns off the homepage so this is its own handler. (6) BIGGER — html.dia-itemv2 sizes #dia-hp-tryon-panel to 400px so the pet preview is comfortable. Click-outside still closes via the 10.199 _haulOnDocDown capture watcher. Item-page-scoped only; homepage/closet TOH untouched. Builds on 10.199. Roll back to 10.199/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.199.0 — THREE ITEM-PAGE Try-On-Haul fixes. (1) The thumbnail "Try On" pill now OVERLAYS the item art at its bottom third (was a below-image flow element sitting under the Lebron tag): the <img> is wrapped in #dtr-thumb-imgwrap (position:relative) and the pill is absolutely-anchored inside it (bottom:12%, centered, drop-shadow for legibility) — so it floats over the art only, never over the Lebron / "Find in:" tags below. (2) Opening Try On from the pill now also builds + reveals the HAUL/staging side panel (#dia-hp-wl-panel) — the "third side panel" that lists the tried-on item so it can be viewed/removed. The item page never ran _dtrBuildTohPanel before, so it now builds that panel with a minimal self-contained context reading the shared DTR_HAUL store. (3) Close-on-blur rebuilt: a capture-phase document mousedown collapses the whole TOH cluster (pet preview + Custom Canvas drawer + staging panel + tophat + save modal) when you press outside it, and never when the press is inside a panel or on the Try On pill — armed only while open. What opens here is the DTI Remix TOH cluster (the customizer pickers live INSIDE #dia-hp-tryon-panel), not a separate native modal. Item-page-scoped only; homepage/closet TOH untouched. Builds on 10.198. Roll back to 10.198/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.198.0 — FIVE contained ITEM-PAGE changes. (1) Removed the sunglasses hide-toggle (data-dtr="hide") from the OWNED/WANTED list tiles + its dead click handler — only the rename pencil rides the tile now (hiding moves off the tile). (2) Lebron (stylisher) link removed from the meta row beside DTI 2020 — the Lebron value tag under the thumbnail makes it redundant; JN Items + DTI 2020 + date kept. (3) OCCUPIES / RESTRICTS now align in a 2-col grid (label | value) via display:contents on the native <section>s, so the RESTRICTS label sits directly under OCCUPIES. (4) Dropped the "Save & Close" button — the action row holds only Save, bottom-right; the bulk-sync wizard now builds its own "Save & Next" advance button since it no longer has .dia-save-close-btn to repurpose. (5) The thumbnail hanger is now an icon + "Try On" pill anchored bottom-center; clicking it LAUNCHES window.openTryOnHaul + seeds this item (item 5b). Standalone TOH edge-tab launchers are hidden on the item page so the pill is the only opener (5c), and a focusout/outside-click watcher closes the TOH panel when focus leaves it (5d). Builds on 10.197. Roll back to 10.197/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.197.0 — FOUR contained fixes. (1) Removed the redundant left-side Offering/Seeking pill badges (#dtr-trade-badges) from the item-info area + their dead click handler — the Trade Activity sidebar already has Offering/Seeking tabs. (2) Trade rows show more: .dia-list-row now wraps to 2 lines (line-clamp) instead of 1-line ellipsis, and .dia-owner-name max-width raised 180->240px so trader names are not needlessly cut. (3) The "Eye" (.dia-visited-status-check seen-indicator) was restyled off its stale green + glow to the konpeito system. (4) Lebron value now says "1 cap" (singular) instead of "1 caps" everywhere a numeric value/total hits exactly 1. Builds on 10.196. Roll back to 10.196/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.196.0 — TWO fixes. (A) Trade Activity SIDEBAR bound-fix: hard max-height + position:sticky so it scrolls inside itself (was align-self:stretch which froze page scroll); widened to 360 + smaller row gutter. (B) Trade tab bar reworked: dropped All/Planned tabs; Offering/Seeking now mutually-exclusive PRIMARY filters (one active, default Offering); Favorites became a separate amber STAR TOGGLE pill (dtr-fav-only on #dia-trade-lists). Builds on 10.195. Roll back to 10.195/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.195.0 — ITEM PAGE restructure: Trade Activity is now a FULL-HEIGHT RIGHT SIDEBAR of the whole card instead of a column inside the header. #dtr-header-split is a flex ROW = [#dtr-main-col (item header + OWNED/WANTED lists, flex:1), #dia-trades-panel (right sidebar, align-self:stretch so it matches the full card height, internal scroll with overscroll-contain)]. This kills the huge empty white gap (header no longer forced as tall as the 480px panel) and reconnects the lists card. Undid the 10.193/10.194 in-header-flex + max-height:480px cap rules; #dia-item-card-v2 is a normal block header again (keeps its dashed border-bottom). Narrow widths stack the sidebar full-width below #dtr-main-col. Also REMOVED the dead main-script #dtr-itemv2-cover (flash is handled by the separate Flash Guard companion now; the main cover ran too late after the 2MB parse). Builds on 10.194. Roll back to 10.194/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.194.0 — FIXES to 10.193: (1) the in-header Trade Activity panel was not capping its height (align-self:stretch + content-driven header let it grow to the full 298-trade list -> card ballooned to ~1200px, huge empty gap, lists shoved to the bottom). Now the PANEL has a hard max-height:480px + overflow:hidden and #dia-trade-lists is the flex scroll box inside it (the .dia-trade-scroll 10.189 max-height:none is neutralized within the panel). (2) green flash STILL showed because the visibility:hidden allowlist guessed the wrong native containers — replaced with a real full-viewport opaque cover (#dtr-itemv2-cover, like the Import Flash Guard) that masks everything until #dia-shell mounts, then removed (+5s failsafe). Builds on 10.193. Roll back to 10.193/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.193.0 — ITEM PAGE: (1) Trade Activity panel relocated into the EMPTY right side of the header card (was a hidden bottom block revealed by a badge click) — now always visible, laid out as a 2-col header (item info left, trades right ~340px), with its OWN contained inner scroll (overscroll-behavior:contain) so the wheel never escapes to the page; the Offering/Seeking badges now just switch the tab in place (no reveal, no scroll-into-view); narrow widths drop it full-width below the header. (2) Green-flash guard for item pages: a dia-itemv2-preactive class + cream background + native-content hide (excludes #dia-shell) prevents the native green item page flashing before the reskin mounts; cleared right after html.dia-itemv2 with a 4s failsafe. Builds on 10.192. Roll back to 10.192/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.192.0 — "Find in:" group: the label now sits on its OWN line with Closet + SDB together on a centered row beneath it (was wrapping to "Find in: Closet" / "SDB"). Builds on 10.191. Roll back to 10.191/.../10.167.
  // prev 10.191.0 — ITEM PAGE: (1) ROOT CAUSE of the off-theme look — the item page was missing the konpeito design tokens, so every var(--…) fell back: fonts→Arial, and colors (--mint-d/--tea-d/--ink) →dark ink (the "Offering/Seeking too dark"). Now the FULL konpeito token set is defined on #dia-shell, 1:1 with the import. (2) Owned/Wished count was 13px (huge next to the 10px label) → now 11px in gray ink, like the import. (3) Closet + SDB moved out of the meta row into a "Find in:" pill group UNDER the Lebron badge. Builds on 10.190. Roll back to 10.190/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.190.0 — ITEM PAGE font fix: the list tiles ARE the import\'s .dib-* component (dibOwnedCellHtml), but they inherit font from #dia-shell, which still carried a legacy font-family:Arial — so the tiles rendered in Arial, not the import\'s Nunito. Defined --f/--fd/--fnum on the item-page scope and forced #dia-shell (+ its controls) onto var(--f); stepper numerals now use DM Mono (--fnum) too. Cumulative: also includes 10.189\'s dashed divider + the Trade Activity scroll-trap fix (.dia-trade-scroll no longer an inner scroller — the PAGE scrolls). Builds on 10.189. Roll back to 10.189/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.189.0 — ITEM PAGE: (1) the header→lists divider is now DASHED (1px dashed var(--line)), matching the import\'s .dib-head exactly — was an off-theme solid line. (2) FIXED the scroll trap: the Trade Activity list was an inner .dia-trade-scroll box (max-height:500px;overflow-y:auto) that captured the wheel — you couldn\'t scroll the page past the panel, and had to mouse off it to scroll back up. Now it flows in the document so the PAGE scrolls (like native DTI); also dropped its legacy #c8e4da green border. Builds on 10.188. Roll back to 10.188/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.188.0 — ITEM PAGE polish: (1) list grid pinned to 3 even columns (was auto-fill → lopsided 4+2 for 6 lists; now clean 3+3). (2) De-greened the nested legacy containers — #dia-item-bar / #dia-work-card carried an old #a8d4c4 GREEN border + #f7f6ef fill (the "green container inside the header"); the merged #dtr-header-split card supplies the surface now. (3) Added Closet + SDB quick-links to the meta row (read-only neopets.com nav by item name; no writes). (4) Softened the trade-activity reveal-scroll — only nudges if the panel is off-screen, block:nearest (was an aggressive block:start that "hijacked" the page). NOTE: the "can\'t scroll back up" trap + the background line on expand still need a live repro to pin. Builds on 10.187. Roll back to 10.187/.../10.167.','color:#e8729b;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;');
  // prev 10.187.0 — single-instance guard (unsafeWindow.__DTR_INSTANCE_ACTIVE__); 2nd copy stands down. [10.188 = item-page 3-col grid + de-green + closet/SDB links + softer trade-scroll]
  // prev 10.185.0 — theme id swept to konpeito across all 199 refs (id/selectors/attrs/label-key/font-fn/contract prose), 3 case-sensitive passes; storage key stays "dib-theme" so a stored old value falls back to the konpeito default — same theme, no migration, no functional change.
  // prev 10.184.0 — notes component restyle to Konpeito tokens. [10.185 = theme id swept to konpeito, no functional change]
  // prev 10.183.0 — Lebron "? caps" for unreported + List-settings modal to <body> (alignment) + import double-scrollbar fix. [10.184 = notes component restyle to Konpeito tokens]
